    "The upcoming discussion will focus on refining these methods and exploring new possibilities in DL for fossil analysis, aiming to improve existing techniques and pioneer new strategies.",
    "Before discussing the trends in classification and segmentation models as presented from the results, it is important to acknowledge several challenges that make it difficult to identify clear trends and perform a fair evaluation of the models.",
    "The immaturity of the field and the lack of benchmarked datasets pose significant hurdles, as different architectures are often trained and evaluated on proprietary data, making direct comparisons impossible.",
    "Furthermore, a consistent problem across studies is the lack of model generalizability, which is primarily rooted in dataset constraints.",
    "The absence of large-scale datasets with broad taxonomic sampling, which could potentially be addressed through community data pooling, limits the robustness of trained models."
